&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE DAY-TO-DAY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define risk-based test plans and acceptance criteria in partnership with Product/Engineering; translate user stories into clear test cases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain automated tests (Cypress/TypeScript preferred) across E2E, integration, and API layers; create reusable utilities/page objects and stabilize flaky tests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and own CI/CD test gates (smoke/regression) with parallelization and clear pass/fail signals; track coverage and test health metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform targeted manual/exploratory testing for new features, edge cases, and UX flows; drive regression for critical paths.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and manage test data, mocks/fixtures, and environment configurations to keep tests deterministic and fast.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with engineers to reproduce, triage, and debug issues using logs/metrics/trace tools; verify fixes and prevent regressions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own post-deploy smoke testing and release sign-off for web apps and mobile apps; document results and risks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously improve the QA/SDET toolchain and practices (coding standards, coverage goals, flake budgets, reporting dashboards).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT MAKES YOU QUALIFIED&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science/Software or related field (advanced degrees a plus).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years in software testing with strong grounding in functional/regression and modern test design techniques (BC, EP, pairwise, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience testing web applications and mobile apps end-to-end, including UX/UAT and bug verification across browsers/devices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years focused on test automation, including designing scalable frameworks and CI integration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with Cypress (preferred) and JavaScript/TypeScript; experience with API testing (Postman/Newman, supertest, REST/GraphQL) and at least one additional tool (Playwright/WebdriverIO/Jest/Mocha).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable with CI/CD (GitHub Actions/CircleCI/GitLab), Git, and basic Docker; familiarity with env management and secrets.&lt;/li&gt;
